Body:
Description: I am trying to add a new file server to the Host Management or to a host list and I get an error of Host List Messages: Could not add hosts from list. 
I am trying to add it manually through the wizard
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Mike Candon, Jason Skidmore

What We've Learned Updated: +++++
2025_0407: Only 1 of these 3 jobs normally takes days to run:
+++++
1) .Active Directory Inv running for 6 days and 10 hours
 
2) Active Directory running for 6 days 13 hours 
 
3) Active Directory Advanced - 3d 5 hours

4) They were running at the same time and locking each other out

Error found in the SADebug.TSV log = transaction log for database 'StealthAudit' is full due to 'ACTIVE_TRANSACTION'.

This is because 3 AD jobs were running (not successfully) at the same time.

5) Killed the 2 AD jobs and 1 .AD Inv job and now he was able to add the host name successfully.
